<item>
            <title>[PIG-1938] support project-range as udf argument</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1938</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With changes in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1693&quot; title=&quot;support project-range expression. (was: There needs to be a way in foreach to indicate &amp;quot;and all the rest of the fields&amp;quot; )&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1693&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1693&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, project-range (&apos;..&apos;) is supported in all use cases where &apos;*&apos; (project-star) is supported, except as udf argument. &lt;br/&gt;
To be consistent with usage of project-star, project-range should be supported as udf argument as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
